events.name: New York Knicks at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham had 36 points and eight assists, lifting the Detroit Pistons to a 115-106 win over the New York Knicks on Thursday night in a possible preview of a first-round matchup in the NBA playoffs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cunningham scores 36, Pistons top Knicks 115-106 in possible preview of 1st-round playoff matchup

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton scored eight of his 23 points during a key scoring run in the fourth quarter and Aaron Nesmith added 22 points to help the Indiana Pacers rally past the short-handed...
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton scores 23, Pacers secure top-four seed in East with 114-112 win over short-handed Cavs

headlines.description: — Zaccharie Risacher scored a season-high 38 points as the Atlanta Hawks routed the Brooklyn Nets 133-109 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Risacher scores season-high 38 points as Hawks beat Nets 133-109

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 28 points and 11 rebounds as the Milwaukee Bucks extended their winning streak to six games with a 136-111 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks extend winning streak to 6 games with a 136-111 win over the Pelicans

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 44 points, including 18 during Minnesota's franchise-record, 52-point third quarter, and the Timberwolves beat the Memphis Grizzlies 141-125 on Thursday night in a game between teams fighting to avoid the play-in tournament.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Edwards scores 44, Wolves pour in 52 points in 3rd and beat Grizzlies 141-125
